<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="352">Note:</emphasis>
The material designated as the type by Oliver, though in Paul 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Hermann’s">Hermann's</normalizedToken>
herbarium, was not from Ceylon and so did not feature in 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Linnaeus’">Linnaeus'</normalizedToken>
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="352">
<volumeTitle>Flora Zeylanica</volumeTitle>
</emphasis>
(1747). However, this South African collection was directly annotated by Linnaeus and is therefore original material for the name.
</paragraph>
